Add a public function called SafeDivide to Calculator.calr that divides two numbers and returns a Result. It takes i32 parameters a and b, returns Result<i32,str>. If b is not zero, return Ok with the result; otherwise return Err.

Use this exact Calor Result Ok return syntax:
§F{f003:SafeDivide:pub}
  §I{i32:a}
  §I{i32:b}
  §O{Result<i32,str>}
  §IF{if001} (!= b 0)
    §R §OK (/ a b)
  §EL{if001}
    §R §ERR "Division by zero"
  §/I{if001}
§/F{f003}

The Result type syntax:
- §R §OK value - returns Ok(value)
- §OK wraps a success value
- Result<T,E> for operations that can fail
